'''Cannabis in Lithuania''' is illegal for recreational and medical purposes, but production of [[industrial hemp]] is permitted.

==Industrial hemp==
In 2013 Lithuania was the only country in the European Union which banned the cultivation of industrial hemp, and in September that year by a vote of 66–16 the government elected to legalize industrial hemp, pending the president's signature and to take effect at the start of 2014.<ref>{{cite web|author=Liepa Želnienė 15min žurnalistė |url=http://www.15min.lt/en/article/business/lithuania-legalizes-industrial-cannabis-527-338194 |title=Lithuania legalizes industrial cannabis &#124; en.15min.lt |publisher=15min.lt |date=2013-05-23 |accessdate=2016-12-11}}</ref>

==2016 protest==
In 2016, protestors planning an [[420 day|April 20th]] event at Parliament were targeted by the Prosecutor General's Office, which believed that permitting the event might "violate the public interest".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baltictimes.com/cannabis_activists_to_gather_in_vilnius/ |title=Cannabis activists to gather in Vilnius |publisher=Baltictimes.com |date=2016-03-31 |accessdate=2016-12-11}}</ref>

