{{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = Dr | name = | honorific_suffix = [[DrMedSci]] | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth year and age|1940}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | monuments = | residence = | nationality = [[Norwegian people|Norwegian]] | other_names = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = [[Nutritional physiologist]] | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | home_town = | television = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = | website = }}
Dr '''Elisabet Helsing''' [[DrMedSci]] (born 1940) is a Norwegian [[nutritional physiologist]].
Helsing attended the University of Oslo, and subsequently wrote on and campaigned for natural [[breastfeeding]].<ref name="HoMBRG">{{cite Q|Q29581763}}</ref>
She joined the [[World Health Organization]] in 1984, working at their regional office for Europe on matters related to nutrition, until 1996.<ref name="HoMBRG" />
She served as president of the 8th European Nutrition Conference; and as president of the [[Federation of European Nutrition Societies]] from 1999 to 2003.<ref name="HoMBRG" />
She was a founder of the Norwegian support group for mothers, {{lang|no|{{illm|Ammehjelepen|WD=Q11957724}}}}, whose first meeting was held in her house in 1968, and which inspired the Swedish equivalent.<ref name="HoMBRG" /><ref name="WAB">{{cite web|title=Mother Support Task Force (MS TF)|url=http://www.waba.org.my/whatwedo/gims/doc/eng_v4n2.doc|publisher=World Alliance for Breastfeeding|accessdate=30 June 2017}}</ref> She is an honorary member of both.<ref name="HoMBRG" /><ref name="WAB" />
She was given the [[Mediterranean Diet Foundation]]'s first [[Grande Covian Award]] in 1996, and received the Norwegian [[King's Medal of Merit]] in Gold, for services to the people in 2003.<ref name="HoMBRG" />
