{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} {{Use British English|date=March 2018}} {{More footnotes|date=March 2010}} '''Maged N. Kamel Boulos''' is a British [[Health Informatics|health informatician]], scientist and Professor of [[Digital Health]] currently based at the Alexander Graham Bell Centre of Digital Health, [[University of the Highlands and Islands]], having worked before that at the [[University of Plymouth]], at the [[University of Bath]] and at [[City University London]]. He is particularly known for his research into [[Geographic Information Systems]] (GIS) applications in health and healthcare, which received wide news media coverage. He is credited with coining the phrases 'online consumer geoinformatics services'<ref>[https://www.webcitation.org/5y4HOGHKW?url=http://classic-web.archive.org/web/20080619172801/http://think.random-stuff.org/FrontPage/archive/2005/10/16/online-consumer-geoinformatics-services]</ref> and 'wikification of GIS by the masses' <ref>[http://www.ij-healthgeographics.com/content/4/1/22]</ref> in 2005, when [[neogeography]] and [[virtual globes]] were still very new.
Kamel Boulos is Founder and Editor-in-Chief of the [[Open access (publishing)|Open Access]], [[MEDLINE]]-indexed ''International Journal of Health Geographics'',<ref>[http://ij-healthgeographics.com/ ''International Journal of Health Geographics'']</ref> published by [[BioMed Central]] since 2002. He is Co-Chair of WG IV/4: Virtual Globes and Context-Aware Visualisation/Analysis<ref>[http://www.isprs.org/technical_commissions/wgtc_4.aspx#wg_IV/4 Co-Chair of WG IV/4: Virtual Globes and Context-Aware Visualisation/Analysis]</ref> within the International Society for Photogrammetry and Remote Sensing (ISPR)<ref>[http://www.isprs.org/ International Society for Photogrammetry and Remote Sensing (ISPRS)]</ref> Commission IV Geodatabases and Digital Mapping, 2008-2012.
